title: Voices.of.a.Generation.Claire.Bloom.PDTV.x264.Hector.mp4
description:
The King's Speech star Claire Bloom reflects on her long and acclaimed career.
 
Claire Bloom discusses her roles in Brideshead Revisited, The King's Speech, Limelight and Crimes and Misdemeanors. She also shares anecdotes about working with Charlie Chaplin and Woody Allen, and discusses her relationships with Richard Burton, Rod Steiger and author Philip Roth. 


Enjoy, Gaz/Hector
